{
  "text": "Nucleic acid sequencing confirmed the homology of the three serotypes: DENV-1, DENV-2 and DENV-3. DENV-1 was the most frequently detected serotype within our study. This serotype was also seen most often in European travellers studied in the years 2002-2008 [CITATION_1] . During the 70 years of studies on dengue serotypes spread and circulation, the majority of cases reported were caused by DENV-1 infection [CITATION_2] .",
  "correct_citation": {
